title: Colorful Barranco Tour and Street Art
description:
Visit the most colorfull district of Peru, Barranco...

Barranco is famous for its bridge of sights, its church and its path down to the beach. The district has a very interesting history, bohemian and artistic lifestyle, murals, street art. If you would like to explore the town for 2 hours and learn about the escense of the district, this is the perfect tour. 

We will meet by stasrbucks in Barranco and start our Barranco Tour by the main square talking about the district history and anecdotes. We will continue walking by the famous ''28 de Julio'' street, Here we will share the true meaning of the murals on the district, the murals can share so many stories that can blow your mind. 

Later, visit the "Bajada de Baños" street, a famous path down to the beach full of plants, trees, art and colors. Here you can cross the famous Bridge of Sights and pass by the Church ''La Hermita''. Finish this fantastic tour by looking at the green coast or coming down to the beach!

We will visit the most important spot in Barranco. We will stop to take photos and explain the history of Barranco, the street art, graffiti and murals.Duration: 10 minutesStop At:Parque Municipal de Barranco, Entre las Avenidas Pedro de Osma y Almirante Miguel Grau Barranco, Lima 15063 PeruWe will begin the tour by walking through the streets and explaining the highlights of Barranco. The Chicha Art, the Magic and Barrancos Fish-MapDuration: 20 minutesStop At:Bajada de los Banos, Municipalidad del Barranco desde el Parque Barranco hasta la Costa Verde., Lima 15047 PeruWalk along Bajada de Baños, through the Hermitage, Bridge of Sighs.Duration: 30 minutesStop At:Puente de los Suspiros, Lima PeruWe will walk across the Bridge of Sighs, a traditional wooden bridge shrouded in an air of romance, having been the place that started countless love affairs in Lima.
It ends on the beach or with a great view of the green coast (or both!)Duration: 20 minutes

reviews.title: Yoced was wonderful.  He was engagingn and informative.  I highly recommend both the guide and the tour!
reviews.text: Yoced was wonderful.  He was engaging, informative and made history fun!  I highly recommend both the guide and the tour!

reviews.title: Excellent fun educational art, culture, history walking tour of Barranco
reviews.text: Our walking tour of Barranco with guide Yoced was superb; it became a private tour as we were the only ones signed up.  He told interesting stories about the history of Barranco, its longtime generous community spirit, e.g., programs held at the library and its plaza, as well as its devastation by Chilean forces.Yoced also helped us appreciate the beautiful and creative street murals by directing our attention to specific features in the paintings and explaining the artists' intentions.  He educated and inspired us so much that we bought a print and t-shirt at the Jade Rivera gallery.Finally, he took a fun video of our crossing the Bridge of Sighs, which turned out to be easy for us even though we're seniors, because of our yoga breathing.Top marks for Yoced and Lima Experience!

reviews.title: Gustavo will give you the lowdown!
reviews.text: We loved learning all about the history of Barranco (as well as wider history of Lima and Peru) during the tour. Our guide Gustavo was very friendly, and able to answer all our questions. There was so much context to some of the street art that we never would have known from walking through by ourselves, so it was great to have a guide as knowledgeable as Gustavo! He also took some lovely photos of us at key spots.I'd highly recommend this tour!

reviews.title: We even went to the Larco Museum, very excellent, he explained how the different societies evolved and finally to Inca.
reviews.text: Joseph (Yoced) did a wonderful job, very knowledgeable about the area, he had a “lock” for us at the Bridge of sighs, nice gesture.

reviews.title: Excellent tour with Yoced
reviews.text: I had the pleasure of taking a one-person tour of Barranco with Yoced.  I had signed up for a group tour but I was the only one who showed. I speak both English and Spanish so he offered to do the tour in either and I wanted some Spanish practice anyway so we had a lovely conversation walking through the murals of the Barranco district. He also gave me a great restaurant suggestion for lunch. Highly recommend

reviews.title: Colorful Barranco Walking Tour is a hit with us.
reviews.text: Joseph was our guide to a small group walking tour of Street Art in the Barranco district. It was great to have Joseph explain the history and significance of many of the colorful street murals. We especially loved the work of artist, Jade Rivera. It’s amazing that simply naming a bridge, the Bridge of Sighs, you can give it a romantic and creative character. We are professional musicians and my sister is a visual artist. We were happy to visit a district that honors and respects artists for the contributions that they make to society.

reviews.title: See art but also learn the context, back story, and history.
reviews.text: Really enjoyed today's tour with Arturo. He provided so much insight and history into what we saw. For example he explained the Jade Rivera mural (which is in 2 sections) that I would never had figured out on my own. Also helped to connect the dots of Peru history with Chile and Barranco's place in that history. Just gave the history and back story of everything that we saw. Talked a bit about his travels to other parts of Peru and life in general. Highly recommend!

Super interesting tour!  I felt like I learned so much in a short period of time. Not only did we discuss the history of Barranco and its murals, but I learned some new things about Lima‘s history and history of Peru as well.  My tour guide was Giovana and it was just me and her on the tour!  She answered all my questions and she even gave me a recommendation for a Peruvian Chinese restaurant in the area that is supposed to be one of the best in town.  The restaurant turned out to be amazing!

reviews.title: Beautiful artwork and talented artist
reviews.text: Peru has some talented artists, there are painted street murals everywhere.  Pictures don't do it justice. It's a great place to take a stroll with family. Kids. Or a partner. There's street vendors everywhere that sell ice cream, pastries, jewelry, clothes, souvenirs, and etc.

reviews.title: Barranco mural tour
reviews.text: Yocedd was so friendly and gave us lots of information about the history of Barranco. He made the tour fun and we had a great time! After the tour he gave us lunch recommendations as well as tips on other things to do while in Lima. The murals were so cool and he gave us the backstory about them.
